{{Infobox film | name = Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood | image = Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood.jpg | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = [[Matt Tyrnauer]] | producer = {{ubl|Matt Tyrnauer|Corey Reeser|Josh Braun}} | writer = | based on = {{Based on|''[[Full Service (book)|Full Service]]''|Scotty Bowers}} | starring = [[Scotty Bowers]] | music = [[Jane Antonia Cornish]] | cinematography = Chris J. Dapkins | editing = {{ubl|Bob Eisenhardt|Daniel Morfesis}} | studio = {{ubl|Altimeter Films|Wavelength Productions|Huntsman Films|Water’s End Productions}} | distributor = Greenwich Entertainment | released = {{Film date|2017|09|09|[[2017 Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|2018|07|27|United States}} | runtime = 97 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = $461,689<ref name="BOM">{{cite web |title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood (2018) |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=scottyandthesecrethistoryofhollywood.htm |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=August 26, 2018}}</ref> }} '''''Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood''''' is a 2017 American [[documentary film]] about the life of [[Scotty Bowers]], who acted as an unpaid [[pimp]] in [[Hollywood]] from the 1940s to 80s. Based on Bowers's book ''[[Full Service (book)|Full Service]]'', it was produced and directed by Matt Tyrnauer, a Special Correspondent for ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altimeterfilms.com/scotty/|title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood|publisher=Altimeter Films}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[2017 Toronto International Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tiff.net/tiff/scotty-and-the-secret-history-of-hollywood/|title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood|website=Tiff.net|language=en|access-date=2018-07-17}}</ref> and was theatrically released on July 27, 2018.<ref>{{citation|title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood {{!}} Greenwich Entertainment|url=https://www.scottymovie.com/|access-date=2018-07-17}}</ref>
==Reception== On the review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 89% based on 62 reviews, with an average rating of 6.9/10. The site's critical consensus reads, "''Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood'' offers plenty of prurient thrills for film fans, but beyond the gossip lies a poignantly illuminating look at decades of sexual mores."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood (2018)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/scotty_and_the_secret_history_of_hollywood/|publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=August 26, 2018}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned the film a normalized score of 67 out of 100, based on 24 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/scotty-and-the-secret-history-of-hollywood |title=Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=August 26, 2018}}</ref>
In his review for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', [[Todd McCarthy]] commented: "What could have been a merely sensationalistic exposé of the private lives of then-closeted screen luminaries instead emerges, in the hands of documentarian Matt Tyrnauer as a nicely filled-out look at different eras, one secrecy-ridden and dedicated to the preservation of illusion, the other wide open and blasé about personal predilections."<ref>{{cite web|last=McCarthy|first=Todd|title=''Scotty and the Secret History of Hollywood'': Film Review|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=September 9, 2017|accessdate=March 13, 2018|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/scotty-secret-history-hollywood-review-1037277}}</ref>
